  "conclusion": "Transvaginal ultrasound demonstrates intrauterine pregnancy with crown-rump length consistent with 9 weeks 4 days gestation. No fetal cardiac activity detected, confirming fetal demise (missed abortion). No adnexal mass or free fluid identified. Findings rule out ectopic pregnancy and hemorrhagic complication; patient is clinically stable.",
